Last updated at 12:01AM, August 13 2013
David Cameron would accept fracking in his own back yard as long as constituents were properly consulted, Downing Street said yesterday.
The Prime Minister’s spokesman refused more than ten times to answer questions about whether Mr Cameron would back fracking in his rural Oxfordshire constituency of Witney should shale gas reserves be found.
However, he said that Mr Cameron’s belief that shale gas exploration should be pursued was “as relevant in his constituency as anywhere else in the country”.
